1. The Intent
What specific problem were you trying to solve with AI?

I encountered several PHP errors while developing the cart page of my SMART MEAL KIT web application. 
The errors included undefined session variables, undefined variables ($cart and $row), and difficulties displaying
food images stored as LONGBLOB in the MySQL database. I also needed guidance on displaying the food name and quantity on the cart page.

2. The Interaction (Prompting)
What was your primary prompt, and did you have to refine it?

My initial prompts were:
"What does this PHP warning mean?"
"How do I fetch an image from the database?"
"How do I display a LONGBLOB image using PHP?"
"Why is my $cart variable undefined?"
"How can I fetch the food name from the database and display it together with the quantity?"

After receiving the explanations, I refined my prompts by sharing my PHP source code and screenshots
of the errors so that the AI could provide more accurate debugging suggestions based on my project.

3. The Output & Verification
Did the AI provide working code? How did you test/verify it?

The AI explained the causes of the PHP errors and provided example code for handling PHP sessions, displaying images stored as LONGBLOB,
and retrieving food information from the database. I tested each suggestion by running the project using XAMPP, refreshing the cart page, and
checking whether the PHP warnings disappeared and whether the food image and details were displayed correctly. I also verified the output using
phpMyAdmin and browser testing.

4. Human Refinement
What changes did YOU make to the AI's code to make it fit your specific project?

I modified the AI-generated examples to match my project's database structure, table names, and column names. I integrated the code
into my existing cart.php file, adjusted the session variable names, updated the SQL queries, and modified the HTML layout and CSS styling
so that the food image, food name, and quantity matched the design of my SMART MEAL KIT web application. I also tested and corrected the code
until it functioned correctly within my project.
